The transfer command t, lets you copy blocks of audio data, replicating
them somewhere else within the stream, so that they exist in both
places: where they were originally, and where you have copied them.
It needs a block address, or a comma separated pair of them, in front
of the command, to tell what blocks to transfer, and a single block
address after it, to tell where to put the copy.  The copied blocks are
appended to the destination block, unless the destination is block one,
when it is inserted ahead of it.

